The paper focuses on analyzing the capabilities and limitations of neural networks for sequence-based signal processing in communication systems. This topic falls under the intersection of several CS sub-categories, including information theory (cs.IT), neural networks (cs.NE), machine learning (cs.LG), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and systems and control (cs.SY). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
